==English==
===Etymology===
Ancient Greek [[πνευμονία]], [[πλευμονία]] ''(pneumonia,''  ''pleumonia'' lung disease), from [[πνεύμων]], [[πλεύμων]] ''(pneumōn, pleumōn'' lungs).  The later spellings in πν- ''(pn-)'' are perhaps influenced by [[πνεῦμα]] ''(pneuma,'' breath).

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''pneumonia'''

#An acute or chronic inflammation of the lungs caused by [[virus]]es, [[bacterium|bacteria]] or other [[microorganism]]s, or sometimes by physical or chemical [[irritant]]s.

